rent near-horizon geometries. We study the extremal D3 brane, which has an AdS5-factored near horizon geometry. We find evidence that such an instability does not arise in this geometry, which bolsters the idea that an AdS2-factored near horizon geometry is crucial for the horizon instability to occur.},
